//1.2 The MAC
quick review:
  HUB:
    repeater, all devices w/the macID can receive
  MAC:
    Media Access Control Address
    48 bits / 6 sets of hex
    hexadecimal 
      Manuf:
        first 3 hexChars are the 
      each hex: 4 binary chars
        each binary char = 8bits
    NIC's use MAC addresses to filter whether to process a frame. 
      
    
    
  Test Tips:
    ipconfig /all

Packet:
  macFrom, 
  macTo, 
  body, 
  CRC
    Cyclic Redundancy Check, 
    if data is bad, then re-send
























































